('w_body_A1_09','shoulder','/ˈʃəʊldər/','noun','어깨','The joint connecting the arm to the upper body.','She rested her bag on her {shoulder}.','그녀는 어깨에 가방을 걸쳤어요.','shoulder','A1','body',1,'shoulder bag strap posture upper body'),
('w_body_A1_10','arm','/ɑːm/','noun','팔','The long part of the body from shoulder to wrist.','He raised his {arm} to ask a question.','그는 질문하기 위해 팔을 들었어요.','arm','A1','body',1,'arm raised hand question classroom'),
('w_body_A1_11','hand','/hænd/','noun','손','The part at the end of the arm including fingers and palm.','She held the book in her {hand}.','그녀는 손에 책을 들고 있었어요.','hand','A1','body',1,'hand holding book palm fingers'),
('w_body_A1_12','finger','/ˈfɪŋɡər/','noun','손가락','Each of the four long thin parts of the hand.','She pointed her {finger} at the map.','그녀는 지도를 손가락으로 가리켰어요.','finger','A1','body',1,'finger pointing map direction gesture'),
('w_body_A1_13','chest','/tʃɛst/','noun','가슴','The front part of the body between the neck and stomach.','He felt a tightness in his {chest}.','그는 가슴에 답답함을 느꼈어요.','chest','A1','body',1,'chest upper body torso anatomy human'),
('w_body_A1_14','stomach','/ˈstʌmək/','noun','배, 위','The organ inside the body that digests food.','Her {stomach} growled because she was hungry.','그녀는 배가 고파서 배에서 꼬르륵 소리가 났어요.','stomach','A1','body',1,'stomach hunger food digest tummy'),
