('w_body_A2_14','cheek','/tʃiːk/','noun','볼, 뺨','Either side of the face below the eye.','Her {cheeks} turned red when she laughed.','그녀는 웃을 때 볼이 빨개졌어요.','cheeks','A2','body',1,'cheek blush smile laugh face'),
('w_body_A2_15','jaw','/dʒɔː/','noun','턱뼈','The lower part of the face that moves when you eat or speak.','He clenched his {jaw} when he was stressed.','그는 스트레스를 받으면 턱뼈를 꽉 다물었어요.','jaw','A2','body',1,'jaw clench stress face anatomy'),
('w_body_A2_16','fingernail','/ˈfɪŋɡəneɪl/','noun','손톱','The hard covering at the end of each finger.','She painted her {fingernails} bright pink.','그녀는 손톱에 밝은 핑크색을 칠했어요.','fingernails','A2','body',1,'fingernail polish pink manicure beauty'),
('w_body_A2_17','spine','/spaɪn/','noun','척추','The column of bones running down the back.','Good posture protects your {spine}.','바른 자세는 척추를 보호해줘요.','spine','A2','body',1,'spine posture back anatomy skeleton'),
