('w_family_A2_13','close','/kloʊs/','adjective','가까운, 친밀한','Having a strong relationship with someone.','She is very {close} to her younger sister.','그녀는 여동생과 매우 가까워요.','close','A2','family',1,'close siblings sisters smiling bond'),
('w_family_A2_14','nephew','/ˈnefjuː/','noun','조카 (남자)','A son of your brother or sister.','Her {nephew} is the same age as her own son.','그녀의 조카와 그녀의 아들은 나이가 같아요.','nephew','A2','family',1,'nephew aunt uncle family child playing'),
('w_family_A2_15','niece','/niːs/','noun','조카 (여자)','A daughter of your brother or sister.','She bought a book for her {niece}''s birthday.','그녀는 조카의 생일 선물로 책을 샀어요.','niece','A2','family',1,'niece family girl birthday gift happy'),
('w_family_A2_16','pregnant','/ˈpreɡnənt/','adjective','임신한','Having a baby growing inside the body.','She announced that she was {pregnant} at the family dinner.','그녀는 가족 저녁 식사 자리에서 임신 소식을 알렸어요.','pregnant','A2','family',1,'pregnant mother expectant family announcement'),
('w_family_A2_17','newborn','/ˈnjuːbɔːrn/','adjective','갓 태어난, 신생아의','Recently born; of or relating to a baby just born.','The {newborn} baby slept in her mother''s arms.','갓 태어난 아기가 엄마 품에서 잠들었어요.','newborn','A2','family',1,'newborn baby hospital mother arms tender'),
('w_family_A2_18','adopt','/əˈdɒpt/','verb','입양하다','To legally take another person''s child as your own.','They decided to {adopt} a child after years of trying.','몇 년간의 노력 끝에 그들은 아이를 입양하기로 결정했어요.','adopt','A2','family',1,'adoption family child love new home'),
('w_family_A2_19','trust','/trʌst/','noun','신뢰, 믿음','A firm belief in someone''s honesty or ability.','{Trust} is the foundation of every healthy relationship.','신뢰는 모든 건강한 관계의 기초예요.','trust','A2','family',1,'trust family bond hands together warm'),
('w_family_A2_20','forgive','/fərˈɡɪv/','verb','용서하다','To stop being angry at someone for something wrong they did.','Learning to {forgive} your family is never easy.','가족을 용서하는 법을 배우는 것은 결코 쉽지 않아요.','forgive','A2','family',1,'forgiveness hands reconcile warm light'),
('w_family_A2_21','protect','/prəˈtekt/','verb','보호하다','To keep someone safe from danger or harm.','Parents naturally want to {protect} their children.','부모는 자연스럽게 자녀를 보호하고 싶어해요.','protect','A2','family',1,'protect parent child safe arms'),
('w_family_A2_22','share','/ʃeər/','verb','나누다, 공유하다','To use, have, or experience something together with others.','The siblings {share} a deep bond and many memories.','그 형제자매들은 깊은 유대와 많은 추억을 함께 나눠요.','share','A2','family',1,'sharing siblings together play outdoor'),
('w_family_A2_23','respect','/rɪˈspekt/','noun','존중, 경의','A feeling of admiration for someone because of their qualities.','She was taught to show {respect} to her elders.','그녀는 어른을 존중하는 법을 배웠어요.','respect','A2','family',1,'respect elders bow family culture'),
('w_family_A2_24','generation','/ˌdʒenəˈreɪʃn/','noun','세대','All the people who were born at about the same time.','Three {generations} of this family have lived in this house.','이 집에는 3대에 걸쳐 이 가족이 살았어요.','generation','A2','family',1,'generations family portrait old young together'),
('w_family_A2_25','anniversary','/ˌænɪˈvɜːrsəri/','noun','기념일, 주년','The date on which a special event happened in a previous year.','They celebrated their parents'' thirtieth {anniversary}.','그들은 부모님의 30주년 기념일을 축하했어요.','anniversary','A2','family',1,'anniversary celebration cake flowers couple'),
('w_family_A2_26','argue','/ˈɑːrɡjuː/','verb','말다툼하다, 언쟁하다','To speak angrily to someone because you disagree.','The siblings {argued} over who should do the dishes.','형제자매들은 누가 설거지를 해야 하는지 말다툼을 했어요.','argue','A2','family',1,'argument siblings conflict talking tense'),
('w_family_A2_27','sibling','/ˈsɪblɪŋ/','noun','형제자매','A brother or sister.','She is the youngest {sibling} in a family of five.','그녀는 다섯 명 가족 중 막내예요.','sibling','A2','family',1,'siblings brothers sisters together portrait'),
('w_family_A2_28','reunion','/riːˈjuːniən/','noun','재회, 동창회, 가족 모임','A social occasion when people who have not met for a long time come together.','The annual family {reunion} is held every summer.','매년 여름에 가족 모임이 열려요.','reunion','A2','family',1,'family reunion gathering outdoor celebration summer'),
('w_family_A2_29','tradition','/trəˈdɪʃn/','noun','전통, 관습','A custom or belief that has been passed down through generations.','Cooking together on New Year''s Day is a family {tradition}.','설날에 함께 요리하는 것은 가족 전통이에요.','tradition','A2','family',1,'family tradition cooking holiday cultural'),
('w_family_A2_30','proud','/praʊd/','adjective','자랑스러운','Feeling very pleased about something you or someone close to you has done.','His parents are so {proud} of his achievements.','그의 부모님은 그의 성취가 정말 자랑스러워요.','proud','A2','family',1,'proud parents graduation celebration smiling'),
('w_family_A2_31','responsible','/rɪˈspɒnsɪbl/','adjective','책임감 있는','Having a duty to take care of something or someone.','As the eldest, she felt {responsible} for her younger siblings.','맏이로서, 그녀는 어린 형제자매들에 대해 책임감을 느꼈어요.','responsible','A2','family',1,'responsible eldest sibling care family'),
('w_family_A2_32','grandchild','/ˈɡrændtʃaɪld/','noun','손자, 손녀','A child of one''s son or daughter.','She reads a story to each {grandchild} at bedtime.','그녀는 잠자리에서 손자 손녀 한 명 한 명에게 이야기를 읽어줘요.','grandchild','A2','family',1,'grandchild grandmother reading bedtime warm'),
('w_family_A2_33','grandparents','/ˈɡrænpeərənts/','noun','조부모','The parents of one''s father or mother.','Her {grandparents} taught her their native language.','그녀의 조부모님은 그녀에게 모국어를 가르쳐 주셨어요.','grandparents','A2','family',1,'grandparents grandchildren family love outdoor'),
('w_family_A2_34','expect','/ɪkˈspekt/','verb','기대하다, 예상하다','To think or believe that something will happen or that someone will do something.','Parents often {expect} their children to follow their advice.','부모는 자녀가 조언을 따르기를 기대할 때가 많아요.','expect','A2','family',1,'expectation parent child conversation guidance'),
('w_family_A2_35','loss','/lɒs/','noun','상실, 죽음으로 인한 슬픔','The feeling of sadness when someone you love dies or leaves.','The family is still dealing with the {loss} of their grandfather.','가족은 아직도 할아버지의 죽음으로 인한 슬픔을 극복하는 중이에요.','loss','A2','family',1,'loss grief memorial candle family sadness'),
('w_family_B1_01','relationship','/rɪˈleɪʃənʃɪp/','noun','관계','The way in which two or more people are connected or feel about each other.','Building a strong {relationship} with your family takes time and effort.','가족과 강한 관계를 쌓는 데는 시간과 노력이 필요해요.','relationship','B1','family',1,'relationship family connection bond warm'),
('w_family_B1_02','commitment','/kəˈmɪtmənt/','noun','헌신, 약속, 책임감','A promise or firm decision to do something; dedication to a relationship.','Marriage requires a deep {commitment} from both partners.','결혼은 두 파트너 모두의 깊은 헌신이 필요해요.','commitment','B1','family',1,'commitment rings marriage promise dedication'),
('w_family_B1_03','independence','/ˌɪndɪˈpendəns/','noun','독립, 자립','The state of being free from the control of others.','Teenagers often need space to develop their {independence}.','십대 청소년은 종종 독립심을 키우기 위한 공간이 필요해요.','independence','B1','family',1,'independence teenager freedom outdoor confident'),
('w_family_B1_04','conflict','/ˈkɒnflɪkt/','noun','갈등, 충돌','A serious disagreement or argument that lasts a long time.','Unresolved {conflict} within a family can cause lasting damage.','가족 내에서 해결되지 않은 갈등은 지속적인 피해를 줄 수 있어요.','conflict','B1','family',1,'conflict family argument tension discussion'),
('w_family_B1_05','reconcile','/ˈrekənsaɪl/','verb','화해하다, 조화시키다','To make peace with someone after a disagreement.','It took years for the brothers to {reconcile} after the argument.','형제가 말다툼 후 화해하기까지 수년이 걸렸어요.','reconcile','B1','family',1,'reconcile handshake family peace resolution'),
('w_family_B1_06','communication','/kəˌmjuːnɪˈkeɪʃn/','noun','소통, 대화','The process of sharing information or feelings with others.','Open {communication} is key to a healthy family life.','솔직한 소통은 건강한 가족생활의 핵심이에요.','communication','B1','family',1,'communication family talking open discussion'),
('w_family_B1_07','boundary','/ˈbaʊndri/','noun','경계, 한계선','A limit that defines what is acceptable in a relationship.','Setting clear {boundaries} helps maintain healthy family relationships.','명확한 경계를 설정하면 건강한 가족 관계를 유지하는 데 도움이 돼요.','boundary','B1','family',1,'boundary limit personal space respect'),
('w_family_B1_08','attachment','/əˈtætʃmənt/','noun','애착, 유대감','A strong emotional bond between two people.','Early {attachment} between a parent and child shapes future development.','부모와 아이 사이의 초기 애착은 미래 발달을 형성해요.','attachment','B1','family',1,'attachment baby mother bond love tender'),
('w_family_B1_09','separation','/ˌsepəˈreɪʃn/','noun','별거, 분리','The state of being apart from someone or something.','The {separation} of the parents was hard on the children.','부모님의 별거는 아이들에게 힘든 일이었어요.','separation','B1','family',1,'separation sadness family apart missing'),
('w_family_B1_10','nuclear family','/ˈnjuːkliər ˈfæməli/','noun','핵가족','A family unit consisting of two parents and their children.','The traditional idea of a {nuclear family} has changed significantly.','전통적인 핵가족 개념이 크게 변화했어요.','nuclear family','B1','family',1,'nuclear family parents children home portrait'),
('w_family_B1_11','extended family','/ɪkˈstendɪd ˈfæməli/','noun','대가족, 확대 가족','A family unit that includes grandparents, aunts, uncles, and cousins.','In many cultures, the {extended family} lives together in one home.','많은 문화권에서 대가족이 한 집에서 함께 살아요.','extended family','B1','family',1,'extended family large gathering portrait home'),
('w_family_B1_12','custody','/ˈkʌstədi/','noun','양육권, 보호권','Legal responsibility for the care of a child, especially after parents divorce.','The court awarded {custody} of the children to their mother.','법원은 아이들의 양육권을 어머니에게 부여했어요.','custody','B1','family',1,'custody legal court family child rights'),
('w_family_B1_13','upbringing','/ˈʌpbrɪŋɪŋ/','noun','양육 방식, 성장 환경','The way in which a child is raised and educated.','Her {upbringing} in a multicultural household shaped her worldview.','다문화 가정에서의 성장 환경이 그녀의 세계관을 형성했어요.','upbringing','B1','family',1,'upbringing childhood home family values'),
('w_family_B1_14','discipline','/ˈdɪsɪplɪn/','noun','훈육, 규율','Training that teaches someone to obey rules or a code of behaviour.','Consistent {discipline} helps children develop self-control.','일관된 훈육은 아이들이 자제력을 키우는 데 도움이 돼요.','discipline','B1','family',1,'discipline parenting rules consistent guidance'),
('w_family_B1_15','patience','/ˈpeɪʃns/','noun','인내심, 참을성','The ability to accept delay or difficulty without becoming upset.','Raising a child requires enormous {patience} and understanding.','아이를 키우는 데는 엄청난 인내심과 이해가 필요해요.','patience','B1','family',1,'patience calm parenting child understanding'),
('w_family_B1_16','affection','/əˈfekʃn/','noun','애정, 다정함','A gentle feeling of fondness or liking for someone.','She showed her children plenty of {affection} growing up.','그녀는 자녀들이 자라는 동안 충분한 애정을 보여줬어요.','affection','B1','family',1,'affection family hug love tender warmth'),
('w_family_B1_17','estranged','/ɪˈstreɪndʒd/','adjective','소원해진, 사이가 나빠진','No longer in contact with someone you were once close to.','He was {estranged} from his family for over a decade.','그는 10년이 넘도록 가족과 소원하게 지냈어요.','estranged','B1','family',1,'estranged distance apart lonely family'),
('w_family_B1_18','milestone','/ˈmaɪlstəʊn/','noun','중요한 사건, 이정표','An important event or stage in life.','The first steps of a baby are a major family {milestone}.','아기의 첫 걸음은 가족의 중요한 이정표예요.','milestone','B1','family',1,'milestone baby first steps family celebrate'),
('w_family_B1_19','admire','/ədˈmaɪər/','verb','존경하다, 감탄하다','To respect and like someone for their qualities or achievements.','She has always {admired} her mother''s strength and courage.','그녀는 항상 어머니의 강인함과 용기를 존경했어요.','admire','B1','family',1,'admire respect mother strength inspiring'),
('w_family_B1_20','heritage','/ˈherɪtɪdʒ/','noun','유산, 전통, 문화적 배경','The traditions and values passed down through generations of a family.','She is proud of her cultural {heritage} and family history.','그녀는 자신의 문화적 유산과 가족 역사를 자랑스러워해요.','heritage','B1','family',1,'heritage culture tradition family history roots'),
('w_family_B1_21','sacrifice','/ˈsækrɪfaɪs/','noun','희생, 헌신','The act of giving up something important for someone else''s benefit.','Parents make many {sacrifices} for the happiness of their children.','부모는 자녀의 행복을 위해 많은 희생을 해요.','sacrifice','B1','family',1,'sacrifice parent giving up family love'),
('w_family_B1_22','bonding','/ˈbɒndɪŋ/','noun','유대감 형성','The process of forming a close emotional connection with someone.','Skin-to-skin contact promotes early {bonding} between parents and newborns.','피부 접촉은 부모와 신생아 사이의 초기 유대감 형성을 촉진해요.','bonding','B1','family',1,'bonding parent newborn skin contact love'),
('w_family_B1_23','nurture','/ˈnɜːrtʃər/','verb','양육하다, 키우다','To care for and encourage the development of someone.','Good parents {nurture} both the mind and heart of their children.','좋은 부모는 자녀의 마음과 감성을 함께 키워요.','nurture','B1','family',1,'nurture parenting growth child care support'),
('w_family_B1_24','parenting','/ˈpeərəntɪŋ/','noun','양육, 부모 역할','The activity of bringing up and caring for a child.','Positive {parenting} techniques help children feel secure and loved.','긍정적인 양육 방식은 아이들이 안정감과 사랑받는 느낌을 갖게 해요.','parenting','B1','family',1,'parenting parent child reading learning home'),
('w_family_B1_25','inheritance','/ɪnˈherɪtəns/','noun','유산, 상속','Money or property that you receive from someone who has died.','The family disputed the {inheritance} after their father passed away.','아버지가 돌아가신 후 가족은 유산을 두고 다퉜어요.','inheritance','B1','family',1,'inheritance will estate legal documents'),
('w_family_B1_26','identity','/aɪˈdentɪti/','noun','정체성','The characteristics that make a person who they are.','Her family greatly shaped her sense of {identity}.','그녀의 가족은 그녀의 정체성 형성에 크게 영향을 미쳤어요.','identity','B1','family',1,'identity self reflection portrait personal'),
('w_family_B1_27','resilience','/rɪˈzɪliəns/','noun','회복력, 강인함','The ability to recover from difficult situations.','Growing up in a close family builds emotional {resilience}.','가까운 가족 안에서 자라는 것은 정서적 회복력을 키워줘요.','resilience','B1','family',1,'resilience strength family together support'),
('w_family_B1_28','sibling rivalry','/ˈsɪblɪŋ ˈraɪvəlri/','noun','형제자매 간의 경쟁','Competition or jealousy between brothers and sisters.','{Sibling rivalry} is normal but can become harmful without guidance.','형제자매 간의 경쟁은 정상적이지만 지도 없이는 해로울 수 있어요.','sibling rivalry','B1','family',1,'sibling rivalry competition brothers jealousy'),
('w_family_B1_29','obligation','/ˌɒblɪˈɡeɪʃn/','noun','의무, 책임','A duty that you have because of your social or moral position.','Many adults feel a strong {obligation} to care for aging parents.','많은 어른들은 연로한 부모님을 돌봐야 할 강한 의무감을 느껴요.','obligation','B1','family',1,'obligation duty care elderly parents'),
('w_family_B1_30','grateful','/ˈɡreɪtfl/','adjective','감사한, 고마워하는','Feeling thankful for something kind that someone has done.','She is deeply {grateful} for the sacrifices her parents made.','그녀는 부모님이 해주신 희생에 깊이 감사해요.','grateful','B1','family',1,'grateful thankful family appreciation warmth'),
('w_family_B1_31','grief','/ɡriːf/','noun','슬픔, 비탄','Deep sadness caused by the loss of someone or something important.','The family shared their {grief} when their grandmother passed away.','할머니가 돌아가셨을 때 가족은 함께 슬픔을 나눴어요.','grief','B1','family',1,'grief loss family sadness memorial candle'),
('w_family_B1_32','advice','/ədˈvaɪs/','noun','조언, 충고','Guidance or recommendations about what someone should do.','She always turns to her mother for {advice} in difficult times.','그녀는 힘든 때마다 항상 어머니께 조언을 구해요.','advice','B1','family',1,'advice guidance mother daughter talking warm'),
('w_family_B1_33','role model','/ˈroʊl ˌmɒdl/','noun','역할 모델','A person who is admired and whose behaviour is copied by others.','Her father has been her greatest {role model} since childhood.','아버지는 어린 시절부터 그녀에게 가장 큰 역할 모델이었어요.','role model','B1','family',1,'role model mentor father inspire admire'),
('w_family_B1_34','empathy','/ˈempəθi/','noun','공감 능력','The ability to understand and share the feelings of another person.','Teaching {empathy} at home leads to more compassionate children.','가정에서 공감 능력을 가르치면 더 배려 깊은 아이가 돼요.','empathy','B1','family',1,'empathy understanding feelings family connection'),
('w_family_B1_35','caregiver','/ˈkeərɡɪvər/','noun','돌봄 제공자, 양육자','A person who regularly looks after a child or a sick or elderly person.','The primary {caregiver} in the family is often the mother.','가족 내에서 주요 돌봄 제공자는 흔히 어머니예요.','caregiver','B1','family',1,'caregiver elderly care helping support compassion'),
('w_family_B2_01','intergenerational','/ˌɪntəˌdʒenəˈreɪʃənl/','adjective','세대 간의','Relating to or involving people from different generations.','{Intergenerational} activities strengthen bonds between grandparents and grandchildren.','세대 간 활동은 조부모와 손자녀 사이의 유대를 강화해요.','intergenerational','B2','family',1,'intergenerational generations grandparents children activities'),
('w_family_B2_02','dynamic','/daɪˈnæmɪk/','noun','역학 관계, 다이나믹','The way in which people or things interact within a group.','Understanding family {dynamics} helps improve communication at home.','가족 역학 관계를 이해하면 가정 내 소통을 개선하는 데 도움이 돼요.','dynamic','B2','family',1,'dynamics family interaction relationship group'),
('w_family_B2_03','dysfunctional','/dɪsˈfʌŋkʃənl/','adjective','기능 장애의, 역기능적인','Not operating normally; unable to function properly.','Children who grow up in {dysfunctional} families may need extra support.','역기능적 가족 내에서 자란 아이들은 추가적인 지원이 필요할 수 있어요.','dysfunctional','B2','family',1,'dysfunctional family stress tension conflict home'),
('w_family_B2_04','estrangement','/ɪˈstreɪndʒmənt/','noun','소원함, 관계 단절','The state of being no longer close or friendly with someone.','Family {estrangement} can result from unresolved conflict over many years.','가족 간의 관계 단절은 수년에 걸친 해결되지 않은 갈등에서 비롯될 수 있어요.','estrangement','B2','family',1,'estrangement distance family apart door closed'),
('w_family_B2_05','reconciliation','/ˌrekənsɪliˈeɪʃn/','noun','화해, 조화','The process of restoring a relationship after a dispute.','The siblings finally achieved {reconciliation} after years of conflict.','형제자매는 수년간의 갈등 끝에 마침내 화해했어요.','reconciliation','B2','family',1,'reconciliation handshake family peace embrace warm'),
('w_family_B2_06','autonomy','/ɔːˈtɒnəmi/','noun','자율성, 자주성','The right or ability to make your own decisions without being controlled.','Teenagers increasingly seek {autonomy} as they move through adolescence.','십대 청소년은 사춘기를 지나면서 점점 더 자율성을 추구해요.','autonomy','B2','family',1,'autonomy independence teenager freedom self'),
('w_family_B2_07','parenting style','/ˈpeərəntɪŋ staɪl/','noun','양육 방식','The overall approach a parent uses to raise their child.','Research shows that {parenting style} has a major effect on child development.','연구에 따르면 양육 방식은 아동 발달에 큰 영향을 미쳐요.','parenting style','B2','family',1,'parenting style approach child development home'),
('w_family_B2_08','codependency','/ˌkoʊdɪˈpendənsi/','noun','공동의존, 과도한 의존 관계','A relationship in which one person is excessively reliant on the other.','Recognising {codependency} in a family is the first step to healing.','가족 내에서 공동의존을 인식하는 것이 치유의 첫 단계예요.','codependency','B2','family',1,'codependency relationship dependency counseling healing'),
('w_family_B2_09','bereavement','/bɪˈriːvmənt/','noun','사별, 애도','The state of loss after a loved one dies.','The family needed professional support during their period of {bereavement}.','가족은 사별의 시간 동안 전문적인 지원이 필요했어요.','bereavement','B2','family',1,'bereavement grief loss memorial candle family'),
('w_family_B2_10','legacy','/ˈleɡəsi/','noun','유산, 레거시','Something that is passed down from a person or family to future generations.','Her grandmother left a {legacy} of kindness and resilience.','그녀의 할머니는 친절함과 회복력의 유산을 남기셨어요.','legacy','B2','family',1,'legacy heritage family history portrait generations'),
('w_family_B2_11','unconditional','/ˌʌnkənˈdɪʃənl/','adjective','조건 없는, 무조건적인','Not subject to any conditions or limitations.','A parent''s {unconditional} love is one of life''s greatest gifts.','부모의 무조건적인 사랑은 삶에서 가장 큰 선물 중 하나예요.','unconditional','B2','family',1,'unconditional love family embrace warm tender'),
('w_family_B2_12','blended family','/ˈblendɪd ˈfæməli/','noun','혼합 가족, 재혼 가족','A family formed by two people with children from previous relationships.','A {blended family} requires patience and mutual understanding.','혼합 가족은 인내심과 상호 이해가 필요해요.','blended family','B2','family',1,'blended family stepparent children together home'),
('w_family_B2_13','foster care','/ˈfɒstər keər/','noun','위탁 양육, 임시 보호','A system in which a child is temporarily placed with another family.','She volunteered as a {foster care} provider for three years.','그녀는 3년간 위탁 양육 제공자로 자원봉사했어요.','foster care','B2','family',1,'foster care child family support home'),
('w_family_B2_14','guardianship','/ˈɡɑːrdiənʃɪp/','noun','후견인 역할, 보호자 자격','The legal right and responsibility to care for a child.','The court assigned {guardianship} of the child to her aunt.','법원은 아이의 후견인 자격을 고모에게 부여했어요.','guardianship','B2','family',1,'guardianship legal family child protection court'),
('w_family_B2_15','counseling','/ˈkaʊnsəlɪŋ/','noun','상담, 심리 치료','Professional guidance given to a person dealing with personal or emotional problems.','The couple sought family {counseling} after months of conflict.','그 커플은 수개월간의 갈등 끝에 가족 상담을 받기 시작했어요.','counseling','B2','family',1,'counseling therapy family session talking professional'),
('w_family_B2_16','mediation','/ˌmiːdiˈeɪʃn/','noun','중재, 조정','The process of using a neutral third party to resolve a dispute.','They agreed to try {mediation} before going to court.','법원에 가기 전에 중재를 먼저 시도해 보기로 합의했어요.','mediation','B2','family',1,'mediation neutral third party discussion resolve'),
('w_family_B2_17','adjustment','/əˈdʒʌstmənt/','noun','적응, 조정','The process of changing your behaviour to deal with a new situation.','Moving to a new country requires a major family {adjustment}.','새 나라로 이사하는 것은 가족 전체의 큰 적응을 요구해요.','adjustment','B2','family',1,'adjustment new home family change adapt'),
('w_family_B2_18','expectation','/ˌekspekˈteɪʃn/','noun','기대, 기대치','A strong belief that something will happen or that someone will do something.','Unspoken family {expectations} can cause unnecessary tension.','말로 표현되지 않은 가족의 기대는 불필요한 긴장을 유발할 수 있어요.','expectation','B2','family',1,'expectation pressure family standards discussion'),
('w_family_B2_19','filial','/ˈfɪliəl/','adjective','자식으로서의, 효도의','Relating to a son or daughter''s duties toward their parents.','In many Asian cultures, {filial} responsibility is deeply valued.','많은 아시아 문화권에서 자식으로서의 책임은 깊이 중시돼요.','filial','B2','family',1,'filial piety respect parents culture elder'),
('w_family_B2_20','cohabitation','/koʊˌhæbɪˈteɪʃn/','noun','동거','The act of living together without being married.','{Cohabitation} before marriage has become more common in many countries.','많은 나라에서 결혼 전 동거가 더욱 일반화됐어요.','cohabitation','B2','family',1,'cohabitation couple living together apartment'),
('w_family_B2_21','self-reliance','/ˌself rɪˈlaɪəns/','noun','자기 의존, 자립심','The ability to rely on yourself rather than depending on others.','Parents aim to build {self-reliance} in their children from an early age.','부모는 어린 나이부터 자녀에게 자립심을 키워주려고 해요.','self-reliance','B2','family',1,'self-reliance independence child learning confidence'),
('w_family_B2_22','vulnerability','/ˌvʌlnərəˈbɪlɪti/','noun','취약성, 상처받기 쉬운 상태','The quality of being exposed to the possibility of being hurt.','Sharing {vulnerability} within a family deepens emotional bonds.','가족 내에서 취약한 면을 나누면 감정적 유대가 깊어져요.','vulnerability','B2','family',1,'vulnerability openness family trust sharing tender'),
('w_family_B2_23','authenticity','/ˌɔːθenˈtɪsɪti/','noun','진정성, 진실성','The quality of being genuine and true to one''s own character.','Living with {authenticity} strengthens family relationships over time.','진정성 있는 삶은 시간이 지나면서 가족 관계를 강화해요.','authenticity','B2','family',1,'authenticity genuine real self family open'),
('w_family_B2_24','trauma','/ˈtrɔːmə/','noun','트라우마, 심리적 상처','A deeply distressing experience that causes lasting emotional damage.','Family {trauma} can be passed down through generations unconsciously.','가족 트라우마는 무의식적으로 세대를 거쳐 전해질 수 있어요.','trauma','B2','family',1,'trauma healing therapy family support recovery'),
('w_family_B2_25','accountability','/əˌkaʊntəˈbɪlɪti/','noun','책임감, 책임지는 자세','Being responsible for your actions and accepting the consequences.','Taking {accountability} is essential to restoring trust in a family.','책임을 지는 것은 가족 내에서 신뢰를 회복하는 데 필수적이에요.','accountability','B2','family',1,'accountability responsibility honest family trust'),
('w_family_B2_26','validation','/ˌvælɪˈdeɪʃn/','noun','인정, 확인, 감정 수용','The act of recognising and accepting someone''s feelings as real and understandable.','Children need {validation} from their parents to build self-esteem.','아이들은 자존감을 키우기 위해 부모로부터 감정적 인정이 필요해요.','validation','B2','family',1,'validation acceptance feelings parent child support'),
('w_family_B2_27','resentment','/rɪˈzentmənt/','noun','억울함, 분노, 원한','A feeling of bitterness or anger towards someone who has hurt you.','Long-standing {resentment} between siblings can damage family bonds.','형제자매 사이의 오래된 억울함은 가족 유대를 해칠 수 있어요.','resentment','B2','family',1,'resentment anger siblings conflict tension'),
('w_family_B2_28','forgiveness','/fərˈɡɪvnɪs/','noun','용서','The act of stopping feeling angry at someone for what they have done.','True {forgiveness} within a family requires honesty and compassion.','가족 내에서의 진정한 용서는 솔직함과 공감이 필요해요.','forgiveness','B2','family',1,'forgiveness peace family embrace reconcile warm'),
('w_family_B2_29','dependency','/dɪˈpendənsi/','noun','의존, 의존 관계','The state of relying on someone else for support or help.','Healthy families encourage growth beyond emotional {dependency}.','건강한 가족은 감정적 의존을 넘어선 성장을 장려해요.','dependency','B2','family',1,'dependency reliance family support growth'),
('w_family_B2_30','emotional support','/ɪˈmoʊʃənl səˈpɔːrt/','noun','정서적 지지','Providing comfort, care, and understanding to someone in need.','Offering {emotional support} during difficult times strengthens family trust.','힘든 시간에 정서적 지지를 제공하면 가족 신뢰가 강화돼요.','emotional support','B2','family',1,'emotional support comfort family embrace care'),
('w_family_B2_31','toxic','/ˈtɒksɪk/','adjective','독성 있는, 해로운, 독성적인','Very harmful or unpleasant; causing damage to relationships.','Recognising a {toxic} family pattern is the first step to change.','독성적인 가족 패턴을 인식하는 것이 변화의 첫 단계예요.','toxic','B2','family',1,'toxic relationship stress harmful conflict distance'),
('w_family_B2_32','enmeshment','/ɪnˈmeʃmənt/','noun','과도한 융합, 경계 없는 관계','An unhealthy situation where family members are over-involved in each other''s lives.','Therapists often identify {enmeshment} as a root cause of boundary issues.','치료사들은 종종 과도한 융합을 경계 문제의 근본 원인으로 파악해요.','enmeshment','B2','family',1,'enmeshment boundaries family therapy entangled'),
('w_family_B2_33','differentiation','/ˌdɪfəˌrenʃiˈeɪʃn/','noun','차별화, 자기 분화','The process of establishing one''s own identity separate from the family.','{Differentiation} from one''s family of origin is a key part of growing up.','원가족으로부터의 자기 분화는 성장의 핵심적인 부분이에요.','differentiation','B2','family',1,'differentiation identity self growth independence'),
('w_family_B2_34','boundaries (psychological)','/ˈbaʊndriz/','noun','심리적 경계','The emotional and mental limits you set to protect your wellbeing.','Healthy {boundaries} allow family members to respect each other''s needs.','건강한 심리적 경계는 가족 구성원들이 서로의 필요를 존중하게 해요.','boundaries (psychological)','B2','family',1,'boundaries psychological limits respect family wellbeing'),
('w_family_B2_35','attachment style','/əˈtætʃmənt staɪl/','noun','애착 유형','The pattern of how a person forms emotional bonds, shaped by early relationships.','Your {attachment style} is often influenced by how you were raised.','애착 유형은 종종 당신이 어떻게 양육되었는지에 의해 형성돼요.','attachment style','B2','family',1,'attachment style secure bond parent early childhood'),
('w_family_C1_01','filial piety','/ˈfɪliəl ˈpaɪəti/','noun','효도, 효심','Respect and duty towards one''s parents and ancestors, especially in Asian cultures.','{Filial piety} is a central value in Confucian family ethics.','효도는 유교적 가족 윤리에서 핵심적인 가치예요.','filial piety','C1','family',1,'filial piety confucian respect ancestors culture'),
('w_family_C1_02','kinship','/ˈkɪnʃɪp/','noun','친족 관계, 혈연 관계','The state of being related to someone; family relationship.','The concept of {kinship} varies significantly across cultures.','친족 관계의 개념은 문화마다 크게 다르게 나타나요.','kinship','C1','family',1,'kinship family network culture connection blood'),
('w_family_C1_03','attachment theory','/əˈtætʃmənt ˈθɪəri/','noun','애착 이론','A psychological theory about how early emotional bonds shape development.','{Attachment theory} explains how parental responsiveness affects children long-term.','애착 이론은 부모의 반응성이 아이에게 장기적으로 어떤 영향을 미치는지 설명해요.','attachment theory','C1','family',1,'attachment theory psychology parent child development'),
('w_family_C1_04','intergenerational trauma','/ˌɪntəˌdʒenəˈreɪʃənl ˈtrɔːmə/','noun','세대 간 트라우마','Psychological trauma that is transferred from one generation to the next.','{Intergenerational trauma} can be healed through awareness and therapy.','세대 간 트라우마는 인식과 치료를 통해 치유될 수 있어요.','intergenerational trauma','C1','family',1,'intergenerational trauma healing generations therapy'),
('w_family_C1_05','socialization','/ˌsoʊʃəlaɪˈzeɪʃn/','noun','사회화','The process by which children learn the norms and values of their society.','The family is the primary agent of {socialization} in early childhood.','가족은 유아기 사회화의 일차적 주체예요.','socialization','C1','family',1,'socialization children learning social norms family'),
('w_family_C1_06','formative','/ˈfɔːrmətɪv/','adjective','형성에 중요한, 발달기의','Having a strong and lasting influence on character or development.','The {formative} years of childhood are shaped largely by family environment.','어린 시절의 형성기는 주로 가족 환경에 의해 형성돼요.','formative','C1','family',1,'formative years childhood development family influence'),
('w_family_C1_07','surrogate','/ˈsʌrəɡɪt/','noun','대리인, 대체 역할을 하는 사람','A person who acts as a substitute for another, especially in the context of family.','The elderly neighbour became a {surrogate} grandmother to the children.','나이 드신 이웃은 아이들에게 대리 할머니가 됐어요.','surrogate','C1','family',1,'surrogate grandmother children bond care warm'),
('w_family_C1_08','genealogy','/ˌdʒiːniˈælədʒi/','noun','족보, 가계도','The study of family history and the tracing of family ancestors.','She spent months researching her family''s {genealogy} online.','그녀는 몇 달 동안 온라인으로 가족 족보를 조사했어요.','genealogy','C1','family',1,'genealogy family tree history ancestors research'),
('w_family_C1_09','succession','/səkˈseʃn/','noun','계승, 상속 순서','The process of inheriting a title, property, or role within a family.','The eldest son was first in line for {succession} of the family estate.','장남이 가족 재산 계승의 첫 번째 순위였어요.','succession','C1','family',1,'succession inheritance family estate eldest heir'),
('w_family_C1_10','consanguinity','/ˌkɒnsæŋˈɡwɪnɪti/','noun','혈연 관계, 혈족 관계','The state of being related by blood; shared ancestry.','Legal systems regulate marriage based on degrees of {consanguinity}.','법 체계는 혈연 관계의 정도에 따라 결혼을 규제해요.','consanguinity','C1','family',1,'consanguinity blood relation family ancestry legal'),
('w_family_C1_11','matrilineal','/ˌmætrɪˈlɪniəl/','adjective','모계의, 어머니 쪽 계통의','Relating to or based on kinship with the mother or the female line.','In a {matrilineal} society, inheritance passes through the mother''s line.','모계 사회에서 상속은 어머니 쪽 계통을 따라 이루어져요.','matrilineal','C1','family',1,'matrilineal mother lineage ancestry culture'),
('w_family_C1_12','patrilineal','/ˌpætrɪˈlɪniəl/','adjective','부계의, 아버지 쪽 계통의','Relating to or based on kinship with the father or the male line.','Many traditional cultures follow a {patrilineal} system of inheritance.','많은 전통 문화권에서는 부계 상속 제도를 따라요.','patrilineal','C1','family',1,'patrilineal father lineage tradition ancestry'),
('w_family_C1_13','developmental stage','/dɪˈveləpməntl steɪdʒ/','noun','발달 단계','A recognized period of change and growth in a person''s life.','Each {developmental stage} presents unique challenges for parents to navigate.','각 발달 단계는 부모가 헤쳐나가야 할 고유한 도전을 제시해요.','developmental stage','C1','family',1,'developmental stage child growth milestone family'),
('w_family_C1_14','psychosocial','/ˌsaɪkoʊˈsoʊʃl/','adjective','심리사회적','Relating to the interaction of social and psychological factors in development.','Erik Erikson described eight {psychosocial} stages of human development.','에릭 에릭슨은 인간 발달의 여덟 가지 심리사회적 단계를 설명했어요.','psychosocial','C1','family',1,'psychosocial development stages life family'),
('w_family_C1_15','fictive kinship','/ˈfɪktɪv ˈkɪnʃɪp/','noun','의사 친족, 선택적 가족','A relationship that resembles family without a biological or legal bond.','Close friends who function as family represent a form of {fictive kinship}.','가족처럼 기능하는 가까운 친구들은 의사 친족의 한 형태예요.','fictive kinship','C1','family',1,'fictive kinship chosen family friends bond chosen'),
('w_family_C1_16','ancestral','/ænˈsestrəl/','adjective','조상의, 선조의','Relating to one''s ancestors or the family lineage from the past.','She returned to her {ancestral} village in search of her roots.','그녀는 자신의 뿌리를 찾기 위해 조상의 마을로 돌아갔어요.','ancestral','C1','family',1,'ancestral village roots heritage culture history'),
('w_family_C1_17','lineage','/ˈlɪniɪdʒ/','noun','혈통, 가계','The people who are related to you who lived before you; ancestry.','She traced her {lineage} back to a royal family in the fifteenth century.','그녀는 자신의 혈통을 15세기 왕족까지 추적했어요.','lineage','C1','family',1,'lineage ancestry heritage family tree history'),
('w_family_C1_18','household dynamics','/ˈhaʊshoʊld daɪˈnæmɪks/','noun','가정 내 역학 관계','The patterns of interaction and power within a home.','Changing {household dynamics} after a new baby can be stressful for everyone.','새 아기가 태어난 후 달라지는 가정 내 역학 관계는 모두에게 스트레스가 될 수 있어요.','household dynamics','C1','family',1,'household dynamics family interaction power home'),
('w_family_C1_19','role differentiation','/roʊl ˌdɪfəˌrenʃiˈeɪʃn/','noun','역할 분화','The way in which different members of a family take on distinct roles.','{Role differentiation} within families often reflects broader cultural norms.','가족 내의 역할 분화는 종종 더 넓은 문화적 규범을 반영해요.','role differentiation','C1','family',1,'role differentiation family structure culture norms'),
('w_family_C1_20','family systems theory','/ˈfæməli ˈsɪstəmz ˈθɪəri/','noun','가족 체계 이론','A theory that views the family as an emotional unit and uses systems thinking.','{Family systems theory} helps therapists understand patterns across generations.','가족 체계 이론은 치료사가 세대에 걸친 패턴을 이해하는 데 도움이 돼요.','family systems theory','C1','family',1,'family systems theory therapy generations patterns'),
('w_family_C1_21','nature vs nurture','/ˈneɪtʃər vəˈnɜːrtʃər/','noun','천성 대 양육 논쟁','The debate over whether genetics or upbringing shapes who we become.','The {nature vs nurture} debate is central to understanding child development.','천성 대 양육 논쟁은 아동 발달 이해의 핵심이에요.','nature vs nurture','C1','family',1,'nature nurture genetics environment development debate'),
('w_family_C1_22','acculturation','/əˌkʌltʃəˈreɪʃn/','noun','문화 적응','The process of adapting to the culture of another group, especially in immigrant families.','Children often experience {acculturation} faster than their immigrant parents.','아이들은 종종 이민자 부모보다 더 빠르게 문화 적응을 경험해요.','acculturation','C1','family',1,'acculturation immigrant family culture adapt new'),
('w_family_C1_23','cultural transmission','/ˈkʌltʃərəl trænsˈmɪʃn/','noun','문화 전수','The process by which cultural norms and values are passed from parents to children.','Storytelling is one of the oldest forms of {cultural transmission}.','이야기 전하기는 가장 오래된 문화 전수 방식 중 하나예요.','cultural transmission','C1','family',1,'cultural transmission stories family heritage values'),
('w_family_C1_24','collective identity','/kəˈlektɪv aɪˈdentɪti/','noun','집단 정체성','A shared sense of belonging and identity among members of a group or family.','Shared rituals help reinforce a family''s {collective identity}.','공유된 의례는 가족의 집단 정체성을 강화하는 데 도움이 돼요.','collective identity','C1','family',1,'collective identity family group belonging together'),
('w_family_C1_25','unconditional regard','/ˌʌnkənˈdɪʃənl rɪˈɡɑːrd/','noun','무조건적 존중','In psychology, accepting and supporting a person regardless of their behaviour.','Providing children with {unconditional regard} builds their sense of worth.','아이들에게 무조건적 존중을 제공하면 그들의 자존감이 형성돼요.','unconditional regard','C1','family',1,'unconditional regard acceptance love therapy self-worth'),
('w_family_C1_26','generativity','/ˌdʒenəˈrætɪvɪti/','noun','생성감, 다음 세대에 기여하려는 욕구','The concern for establishing and guiding the next generation.','Erikson described {generativity} as a key goal of middle adulthood.','에릭슨은 생성감을 중년기의 핵심 목표로 설명했어요.','generativity','C1','family',1,'generativity mentor parent legacy guide generation'),
('w_family_C1_27','relational','/rɪˈleɪʃənl/','adjective','관계적인, 관계에 관한','Concerning the way in which people relate to each other.','Family wellbeing is primarily {relational}, not material.','가족의 안녕은 물질적인 것보다 주로 관계적인 것이에요.','relational','C1','family',1,'relational family connection bond communication warm'),
('w_family_C1_28','interpersonal conflict','/ˌɪntəˈpɜːrsənl ˈkɒnflɪkt/','noun','대인 갈등','Conflict that occurs between two or more people in a relationship.','Unresolved {interpersonal conflict} in a family can escalate over time.','가족 내 해결되지 않은 대인 갈등은 시간이 지나면서 심화될 수 있어요.','interpersonal conflict','C1','family',1,'interpersonal conflict family argument resolution'),
('w_family_C1_29','affiliation','/əˌfɪliˈeɪʃn/','noun','소속감, 연계','The state of being connected or associated with a particular group or family.','A sense of {affiliation} within a family provides security and belonging.','가족 내의 소속감은 안정감과 소속의 느낌을 제공해요.','affiliation','C1','family',1,'affiliation belonging family group security connection'),
('w_family_C1_30','clan','/klæn/','noun','씨족, 가문, 일족','A large group of families that share a common ancestor.','The McKenzie {clan} gathered every year for a traditional highland festival.','매킨지 씨족은 매년 전통 고지대 축제에 모였어요.','clan','C1','family',1,'clan family gathering tradition heritage cultural'),
('w_family_C1_31','bequest','/bɪˈkwest/','noun','유증, 유산으로 남기는 것','Something, especially money or property, that you leave to someone in your will.','She left a {bequest} to her grandchildren for their education.','그녀는 손자녀들의 교육을 위한 유산을 남겼어요.','bequest','C1','family',1,'bequest will inheritance legal estate property'),
('w_family_C1_32','enduring bond','/ɪnˈdjʊərɪŋ bɒnd/','noun','지속적인 유대','A connection between people that persists through time and adversity.','Despite the distance, they maintained an {enduring bond} as a family.','멀리 떨어져 있었지만, 그들은 가족으로서 지속적인 유대를 유지했어요.','enduring bond','C1','family',1,'enduring bond family connection lasting love warmth'),
('w_family_C1_33','psychological inheritance','/ˌsaɪkəˈlɒdʒɪkl ɪnˈherɪtəns/','noun','심리적 유산','The emotional patterns, beliefs, and behaviours passed down through a family.','Therapists help clients understand their {psychological inheritance} from parents.','치료사는 내담자가 부모로부터의 심리적 유산을 이해하도록 도와요.','psychological inheritance','C1','family',1,'psychological inheritance patterns family therapy beliefs'),
('w_family_C1_34','domestic sphere','/dəˈmestɪk sfɪər/','noun','가정 영역, 사적 영역','The realm of home and family life, often contrasted with public life.','Historically, women were confined to the {domestic sphere}.','역사적으로 여성들은 가정 영역에 국한되어 있었어요.','domestic sphere','C1','family',1,'domestic sphere home family roles historical culture'),
('w_family_C1_35','gender role','/ˈdʒendər roʊl/','noun','성 역할','The set of behaviours and attitudes considered appropriate for a particular gender.','{Gender roles} within families have shifted significantly over recent decades.','가족 내 성 역할은 최근 수십 년간 크게 변화했어요.','gender role','C1','family',1,'gender role family expectation change modern equality'),
('w_family_C2_01','primogeniture','/ˌpraɪmoʊˈdʒenɪtʃər/','noun','장자 상속 제도','The right of the firstborn child to inherit the parents'' estate.','Under {primogeniture}, all property passed to the eldest son.','장자 상속 제도 하에서 모든 재산은 장남에게 넘어갔어요.','primogeniture','C2','family',1,'primogeniture firstborn inheritance estate eldest'),
('w_family_C2_02','agnatic','/æɡˈnætɪk/','adjective','부계의, 아버지 쪽 친족의','Relating to kinship through the male or paternal line.','{Agnatic} descent systems privilege relationships traced through the father.','부계 혈통 체계는 아버지를 통해 추적되는 관계를 중시해요.','agnatic','C2','family',1,'agnatic paternal lineage ancestry male descent'),
('w_family_C2_03','endogamy','/enˈdɒɡəmi/','noun','같은 집단 내 결혼, 내혼제','The practice of marrying within one''s own social or ethnic group.','{Endogamy} was common in royal families to maintain bloodline purity.','내혼제는 혈통 순수성을 유지하기 위해 왕족에서 흔했어요.','endogamy','C2','family',1,'endogamy marriage culture group tradition social'),
('w_family_C2_04','exogamy','/ekˈsɒɡəmi/','noun','외혼제, 다른 집단과의 결혼','The custom of marrying outside one''s own tribe or community.','Many cultures practise {exogamy} to strengthen alliances between groups.','많은 문화권에서 집단 간 동맹을 강화하기 위해 외혼제를 실천해요.','exogamy','C2','family',1,'exogamy marriage alliance culture tribe community'),
('w_family_C2_05','matrifocal','/ˌmætrɪˈfoʊkl/','adjective','모계 중심의, 어머니 중심의','Centred on the mother or on females within the family structure.','In many Caribbean societies, the family structure is {matrifocal}.','많은 카리브 사회에서 가족 구조는 어머니 중심이에요.','matrifocal','C2','family',1,'matrifocal mother centered family structure culture'),
('w_family_C2_06','bilateral descent','/baɪˈlætərəl dɪˈsent/','noun','양계 혈통 제도','A system of kinship in which descent is traced through both parents.','Most Western societies use a {bilateral descent} system.','대부분의 서구 사회는 양계 혈통 제도를 사용해요.','bilateral descent','C2','family',1,'bilateral descent kinship both parents lineage system'),
('w_family_C2_07','conjugal bond','/ˈkɒndʒʊɡl bɒnd/','noun','부부 유대','The emotional and legal bond between married partners.','The strength of the {conjugal bond} affects the entire family system.','부부 유대의 강도는 전체 가족 시스템에 영향을 미쳐요.','conjugal bond','C2','family',1,'conjugal bond marriage couple commitment legal'),
('w_family_C2_08','nuclear ideology','/ˈnjuːkliər aɪˈdɒlədʒi/','noun','핵가족 이데올로기','The cultural belief that the nuclear family is the ideal family structure.','{Nuclear ideology} has been critiqued for excluding diverse family forms.','핵가족 이데올로기는 다양한 가족 형태를 배제한다는 비판을 받아왔어요.','nuclear ideology','C2','family',1,'nuclear ideology family structure culture social norms'),
('w_family_C2_09','avuncular','/əˈvʌŋkjʊlər/','adjective','삼촌·외삼촌 같은, 친근하고 다정한','Relating to an uncle; kind and friendly in the manner of an uncle.','His {avuncular} warmth made all the younger cousins adore him.','그의 삼촌 같은 따뜻함은 모든 어린 사촌들이 그를 좋아하게 만들었어요.','avuncular','C2','family',1,'avuncular uncle warmth friendly family kind'),
('w_family_C2_10','affinal','/əˈfaɪnl/','adjective','혼인으로 맺어진','Related by marriage rather than by blood.','In-laws are considered {affinal} relatives under kinship terminology.','시가 또는 처가 친척은 친족 용어상 혼인 친족으로 분류돼요.','affinal','C2','family',1,'affinal marriage in-law kinship relation'),
('w_family_C2_11','consanguineal','/ˌkɒnsæŋˈɡwɪniəl/','adjective','혈연의, 혈족의','Related by blood; descended from a common ancestor.','{Consanguineal} relationships form the core of most traditional kinship systems.','혈연 관계는 대부분의 전통적인 친족 체계의 핵심을 이뤄요.','consanguineal','C2','family',1,'consanguineal blood relation ancestry kinship system'),
('w_family_C2_12','patrimonial','/ˌpætrɪˈmoʊniəl/','adjective','세습의, 가산의','Relating to property or rights inherited from one''s father or ancestors.','The {patrimonial} estate was divided among the children after the father died.','아버지가 돌아가신 후 세습 재산이 자녀들에게 분배됐어요.','patrimonial','C2','family',1,'patrimonial estate inheritance father property heritage'),
('w_family_C2_13','matriarchal lineage','/ˌmeɪtriˈɑːrkl ˈlɪniɪdʒ/','noun','모계 혈통','A line of descent traced through female ancestors.','In societies with {matriarchal lineage}, property is inherited through women.','모계 혈통 사회에서 재산은 여성을 통해 상속돼요.','matriarchal lineage','C2','family',1,'matriarchal lineage women ancestry descent culture'),
('w_family_C2_14','kinship network','/ˈkɪnʃɪp ˈnetwɜːrk/','noun','친족 네트워크','The web of social relationships formed by family ties.','The extended {kinship network} provided support during the family crisis.','확대된 친족 네트워크는 가족 위기 동안 지원을 제공했어요.','kinship network','C2','family',1,'kinship network family social relationships support'),
('w_family_C2_15','structural functionalism','/ˈstrʌktʃərəl ˈfʌŋkʃənlɪzəm/','noun','구조 기능주의','A sociological perspective that sees the family as performing key roles in society.','{Structural functionalism} views the family as essential for social stability.','구조 기능주의는 가족을 사회 안정에 필수적인 것으로 봐요.','structural functionalism','C2','family',1,'structural functionalism sociology theory society family'),
('w_family_C2_16','attachment disruption','/əˈtætʃmənt dɪsˈrʌpʃn/','noun','애착 단절, 애착 방해','The interruption of the process of forming secure early bonds.','Prolonged separation from parents can cause {attachment disruption} in infants.','부모와의 장기적인 분리는 영아에게 애착 단절을 유발할 수 있어요.','attachment disruption','C2','family',1,'attachment disruption infant separation anxiety psychology'),
('w_family_C2_17','reproductive labor','/rɪˈprɒdʌktɪv ˈleɪbər/','noun','재생산 노동, 돌봄 노동','The unpaid work of caring for a family, including childcare and housework.','{Reproductive labor} remains disproportionately distributed between genders.','재생산 노동은 여전히 성별 간에 불균등하게 분배돼 있어요.','reproductive labor','C2','family',1,'reproductive labor care work gender domestic equality'),
('w_family_C2_18','symbolic interactionism','/ˈsɪmbɒlɪk ˌɪntərˈækʃənɪzəm/','noun','상징적 상호작용론','A sociological theory that focuses on meanings created through social interaction.','{Symbolic interactionism} examines how family meanings are constructed daily.','상징적 상호작용론은 가족의 의미가 일상 속에서 어떻게 구성되는지 탐구해요.','symbolic interactionism','C2','family',1,'symbolic interactionism sociology meaning family daily'),
('w_family_C2_19','marital dissolution','/ˈmærɪtl ˌdɪsəˈluːʃn/','noun','혼인 해소, 이혼','The legal ending of a marriage; divorce.','{Marital dissolution} rates have risen significantly in the past five decades.','혼인 해소율은 지난 50년간 크게 증가했어요.','marital dissolution','C2','family',1,'marital dissolution divorce legal separation family'),
('w_family_C2_20','heteronormative','/ˌhetərəʊˈnɔːrmətɪv/','adjective','이성애 규범적인','Relating to a worldview that promotes heterosexuality as the normal family structure.','Critics argue that {heteronormative} family models exclude many diverse households.','비평가들은 이성애 규범적 가족 모델이 많은 다양한 가정을 배제한다고 주장해요.','heteronormative','C2','family',1,'heteronormative family model diversity inclusion norms'),
('w_family_C2_21','normative family','/ˈnɔːrmətɪv ˈfæməli/','noun','규범적 가족 모델','The culturally accepted model of what a family should look like.','The concept of the {normative family} has changed dramatically in recent years.','최근 몇 년간 규범적 가족 개념이 크게 변화했어요.','normative family','C2','family',1,'normative family model culture ideal society'),
('w_family_C2_22','domestic ideology','/dəˈmestɪk aɪˈdɒlədʒi/','noun','가정 이데올로기','The set of beliefs about the ideal roles within the home and family.','Victorian {domestic ideology} sharply divided public and private roles by gender.','빅토리아 시대의 가정 이데올로기는 공적·사적 역할을 성별로 엄격하게 구분했어요.','domestic ideology','C2','family',1,'domestic ideology roles gender home historical'),
('w_family_C2_23','ancestral trauma','/ænˈsestrəl ˈtrɔːmə/','noun','조상의 트라우마, 세습 트라우마','Psychological wounds experienced by ancestors that affect later generations.','Research into epigenetics sheds light on how {ancestral trauma} is inherited.','후생유전학 연구는 조상의 트라우마가 어떻게 유전되는지 밝혀주고 있어요.','ancestral trauma','C2','family',1,'ancestral trauma epigenetics inherited generations healing'),
('w_family_C2_24','family systems theory (Bowen)','/ˈfæməli ˈsɪstəmz ˈθɪəri/','noun','보웬의 가족 체계 이론','Murray Bowen''s framework for understanding emotional processes within families.','Bowen''s {family systems theory} introduced the concept of differentiation of self.','보웬의 가족 체계 이론은 자기 분화 개념을 도입했어요.','family systems theory (Bowen)','C2','family',1,'Bowen family systems theory differentiation therapy'),
('w_family_C2_25','triangulation (family)','/traɪˌæŋɡjʊˈleɪʃn/','noun','삼각관계 (가족 내)','The process where a third person is drawn into a two-person conflict to reduce tension.','Therapists identify {triangulation} as a common but unhealthy family pattern.','치료사들은 삼각관계를 흔하지만 건강하지 않은 가족 패턴으로 파악해요.','triangulation (family)','C2','family',1,'triangulation family conflict third party therapy'),
('w_family_C2_26','scapegoating','/ˈskeɪpɡoʊtɪŋ/','noun','희생양 만들기','The practice of blaming one family member for problems affecting the whole family.','{Scapegoating} in a family often masks deeper systemic dysfunction.','가족 내 희생양 만들기는 종종 더 깊은 체계적 역기능을 감추어요.','scapegoating','C2','family',1,'scapegoating blame family dysfunction therapy pattern'),
('w_family_C2_27','emotional cutoff','/ɪˈmoʊʃənl ˈkʌtɒf/','noun','감정적 단절','Bowen''s term for managing anxiety by distancing oneself from the family of origin.','{Emotional cutoff} may reduce tension but prevents true resolution.','감정적 단절은 긴장을 줄일 수 있지만 진정한 해결을 방해해요.','emotional cutoff','C2','family',1,'emotional cutoff distance family Bowen anxiety'),
('w_family_C2_28','multigenerational transmission','/ˌmʌltiˌdʒenəˈreɪʃənl trænsˈmɪʃn/','noun','다세대 전달 과정','The process by which patterns of anxiety and functioning are passed through generations.','Bowen described {multigenerational transmission} as a gradual differentiation process.','보웬은 다세대 전달 과정을 점진적인 분화 과정으로 설명했어요.','multigenerational transmission','C2','family',1,'multigenerational transmission Bowen patterns family'),
('w_family_C2_29','undifferentiated','/ˌʌndɪˈferənʃieɪtɪd/','adjective','미분화된, 자아 분화가 안 된','Not having a clearly developed sense of self separate from one''s family.','An {undifferentiated} person struggles to separate their feelings from others''.','미분화된 사람은 자신의 감정을 타인의 감정과 분리하는 데 어려움을 겪어요.','undifferentiated','C2','family',1,'undifferentiated self family fusion boundaries therapy'),
('w_family_C2_30','parentification','/pəˌrentɪfɪˈkeɪʃn/','noun','부모화, 자녀의 역할 역전','A process where a child is forced to take on adult or parenting responsibilities.','{Parentification} places an unfair emotional burden on children.','부모화는 아이들에게 불공평한 감정적 부담을 지워요.','parentification','C2','family',1,'parentification child role reversal burden responsibility'),
('w_family_C2_31','infantilization','/ɪnˌfæntɪlaɪˈzeɪʃn/','noun','유아화, 어른을 어린이처럼 대우하기','The act of treating a person as if they are younger or less capable than they are.','{Infantilization} within families can prevent adults from developing independence.','가족 내 유아화는 성인이 독립성을 키우는 것을 방해할 수 있어요.','infantilization','C2','family',1,'infantilization family adult child dependency control'),
('w_family_C2_32','role reversal','/roʊl rɪˈvɜːrsl/','noun','역할 역전','A situation where the usual roles are switched, especially between parent and child.','{Role reversal} occurs when a child becomes the primary caregiver for a parent.','자녀가 부모의 주요 돌봄 제공자가 될 때 역할 역전이 발생해요.','role reversal','C2','family',1,'role reversal parent child caregiver burden family'),
('w_family_C2_33','psychodynamic','/ˌsaɪkoʊdaɪˈnæmɪk/','adjective','정신역동적','Relating to the interplay of unconscious mental processes, especially in family therapy.','A {psychodynamic} approach to family therapy explores unconscious patterns.','가족 치료에 대한 정신역동적 접근은 무의식적 패턴을 탐구해요.','psychodynamic','C2','family',1,'psychodynamic therapy family unconscious patterns'),
('w_family_C2_34','object relations','/ˈɒbdʒɪkt rɪˈleɪʃnz/','noun','대상 관계 이론','A branch of psychoanalytic theory focused on how early relationships shape the psyche.','{Object relations} theory helps explain why adults repeat family patterns.','대상 관계 이론은 어른들이 왜 가족 패턴을 반복하는지 설명하는 데 도움이 돼요.','object relations','C2','family',1,'object relations theory psychoanalysis early relationships'),
('w_family_C2_35','transitional object','/trænˈzɪʃənl ˈɒbdʒɪkt/','noun','전이 대상 (예: 인형, 담요)','An object, such as a toy or blanket, that a child uses for comfort and security.','Winnicott described the {transitional object} as a bridge between self and other.','위니캇은 전이 대상을 자아와 타인 사이의 다리로 설명했어요.','transitional object','C2','family',1,'transitional object toy blanket comfort child security')
ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;

